<%= render 'shared/campaign_canonical' %>

<div class="l-constrained">
  <article>
    <div class="l-campaign__content l-campaign__content--padded-top">
      <%= heading_tag 'Start living your life free of debt', class: 'l-campaign__heading', level: 1 %>
      <p>
        Now that you’ve cleared your debts, it’s important to take stock and make sure you have everything you need to continue living a life free of money worries.
      </p>
      <p>
        Whether your goals for the future are to get into good savings habits, apply for a mortgage, or continue improving your credit score, our guides can help you with the information you need to get there.
      </p>
      <p>
        By now you’ve certainly had plenty of experience with budgeting and managing your finances – and you can use our <a href="/en/tools/budget-planner"> Budget planner</a> to make your plan to stay on track even easier. You can save it so you can review it as often as you like.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you’re planning a big purchase or if you want to build up a savings safety net, use our <a href="/en/tools/savings-calculator">calculators</a> to help you work out how much you’ll need to put away each month.
      </p>
      <p>
        Now that you’re debt-free, you may wish to look at ways to improve your credit rating. Having a better score may also help you achieve your future financial goals such as getting a loan to buy a car or successfully applying for a mortgage. Read our guide on <a href="/en/action_plans/how-to-improve-your-credit-rating">How to improve your credit rating</a>, and find out how to check your credit report for free.
      </p>
      <p>
        Learn more about everything you need to stay debt-free:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Should you switch your <a href="/en/articles/how-to-choose-the-right-bank-account">bank account?</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          What are the differences between <a href="/en/articles/good-debt-versus-bad-debt">Good debt and bad debt?</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          Work out the <a href="/en/articles/how-to-work-out-the-true-cost-of-borrowing">True cost of borrowing</a> before applying for any new credit
        </li>
      </ul>

      <div class="callout">
        <%= heading_tag 'Who is MA anyway?', level: 3 %>
        <p>
          We’re the Money Advice Service, an independent service set up by government to help people like you make the most of your money.
        </p>
        <p>
          We give free, unbiased money advice online, on webchat, over the phone, in printed guides and face to face.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <section class="l-campaign__next-steps">
      <%= heading_tag 'Next steps', class: 'l-campaign__next-steps-heading', level: 2 %>

      <div class="next-step">
        <a class="next-step__link" href="/en/tools/budget-planner">
          <%= heading_tag 'Plan ahead', level: 2, class: 'next-step__heading' %>
          <p class="next-step__content">
            Use our Budget planner to calculate your costs and see how much you have left over each month.
          </p>
        </a>
      </div>

      <div class="next-step">
        <a class="next-step__link" href="/en/action_plans/set-and-reach-your-savings-goal">
          <%= heading_tag 'Set a goal', level: 2, class: 'next-step__heading' %>
          <p class="next-step__content">
            People who have a savings goal save more than people who don’t. Set your goal today.
          </p>
        </a>
      </div>

      <div class="next-step">
        <a class="next-step__link" href="/en/action_plans/how-to-improve-your-credit-rating">
          <%= heading_tag 'Be prepared', level: 2, class: 'next-step__heading' %>
          <p class="next-step__content">
            Learn out how to improve your credit rating and find out how to get your free credit report.
          </p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
</div>

<%= render 'shared/campaign_trust_banner' %>

